                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d831">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 B.W./10–1244: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-12T22:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 12, 1944—10 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 13—8:50 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3914. ReEmbs 3900, October 11, 8 p.m. I have received a letter from Molotov dated
                    October 12 enclosing a copy of the text of the preliminary condition as signed
                    in Moscow on October 11 by the delegates of Regent Horthy.</p>
                <p>No change was made in the wording of the condition as proposed by the Russians
                    (see my 3816, October 6, 8 p.m.).</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
